description:
In 1990, actor Dirk Benedict was facing dark times. The A-Team had been canceled a few years earlier and, well, there wasn't much for this debonair thespian of stage and screen to assign his name to. Thus, he had to get by in life by actually pretending to BE the Faceman: conning his way into the hearts and pads of old ladies in order to steal their valuables, which he then pawned at the local shop. And then, one fateful day, a promising offer was slipped under the door of his agent (OK, his landlord), Murray. It read &quot;Will pay Mr. Benadickt [sic] $500 to do a workout video.&quot; Knowing full well that Dirk's rent was behind further than the other ten out-of-work television actors living in his tiny squalid, roach-infested apartment complex, Murray went ahead and forged the good Mr. Benedict's name, went and woke up his unconscious slummer from his alcoholic stupor, and &quot;reminded&quot; him it was time to get to work.

The result: STEEL STOMACHS. Here, one can witness an always-embarrassed (and fiercely heterosexual) Dirk Benedict prance about in tube socks and the most unflattering pair of shorts ever sewn together by an Indian child labor sweatshop - and laugh every second of the way.

